What you need to know:  Middle distance runner Chebichi ran barefoot, wearing just a petticoat, and won her first race in 1973Another barefoot sensation was Rose Tata-Muya who told me recently how she ran barefoot in Mombasa in 1975 while wearing just a petticoatTecla Chemabwai, a pioneer female runner, also impressed in track and field events. She competed at the 1968 Olympic Games in Mexico but did not go past the heats